SIMPLE: transcend
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transcend
<hw>Tran*scend"</hw> <pr>(tr⟦acr⟧n*s⟦ecr⟧nd")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Transcended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Transcending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>transcendere</ets>, <ets>transcensum</ets>; <ets>trans</ets>
beyond, over + <ets>scandere</ets> to climb. See <er>Scan</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To rise above; to surmount; <as>as, lights in the
heavens <ex>transcending</ex> the region of the clouds</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass over; to go beyond; to exceed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such popes as shall <qex>transcend</qex> their limits.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1528 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>To surpass; to outgo; to excel; to exceed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How much her worth <qex>transcended</qex> all her kind.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transcend</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transcend
<hw>Tran*scend"</hw> <pr>(tr⟦acr⟧n*s⟦ecr⟧nd")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To climb; to mount.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be transcendent; to excel.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transcendency</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Transcendence</ent>⟦br⟧
